Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry all produce.

Trim, peel, and cut @carrots{12%ounce}(trimmed, peeled, and cut on a diagonal into ½-inch-thick pieces). Peel and mince or grate @ginger{1%thumb}(peeled and minced or grated). Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}(trimmed and thinly sliced), separating whites from greens.

Toss carrots on a #baking sheet{} with a large drizzle of @cooking oil{}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}. Roast on top rack until tender, ~{20-25%minutes}.

Carefully toss carrots with @sesame seeds{1%tablespoon}.

While carrots roast, heat a drizzle of oil in a #small pot{} over medium-high heat. Add ginger and scallion whites; cook, stirring, until fragrant, ~{1%minute}.

Stir in @jasmine rice{½%cup} and ¾ cup water (1¼ cups for 4 servings). Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce heat to low. Cook until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}. Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

Meanwhile, pat @pork cutlets{12%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}.

Place @panko breadcrumbs{½%cup}, @garlic powder{1%teaspoon}, salt (we used ¾ tsp), and pepper in a #gallon-size zip-close bag{}. (For 4 servings, use 1 1/2 tsp salt.)

Place @sour cream{2%tablespoon} in a #medium bowl{}; add pork and turn to evenly coat.

Add coated pork to #zip-close bag{} with seasoned panko and seal to close. Shake until pork is evenly coated.

> TIP: You may need to move around cutlets in bag, pressing with your hands, to spread out panko and make it stick.

Heat a ¼-inch layer of @cooking oil{1%tablespoon} in a #large nonstick pan{} over medium-high heat. Once oil is shimmering and hot enough that a pinch of panko sizzles when added to the pan, add crusted pork (discard any panko in bag that doesn't stick).

Cook until panko is golden brown and pork is cooked through, ~{2-3%minutes} per side. (For 4 servings, cook in batches.)

Transfer to a paper-towel-lined #plate{}.

Place @katsu sauce{4%tablespoon} in a #small microwave-safe bowl{}; microwave until warmed through, ~{30%seconds}.

Fluff rice with a #fork{}; stir in @butter{1%tablespoon} (2 TBSP for 4 servings) and season with salt and pepper.

Divide rice, pork, and carrots between plates. Drizzle pork with katsu sauce. Sprinkle with scallion greens and serve.